Scribing allows the alchemist to create magical scrolls from base components.

In order to scribe, the alchemist will have to gather 3 separate items.  The
first is a simple blank parchment suitable for scribing.  Such parchments must 
have been specially prepared or the magical properties of the scroll will fade,
so not just any parchment may be used.  The parchment is used to write the scroll.

Secondly, a spell component corresponding to the scroll being created must
be obtained.  One charge of the spell component will be utilized during
scribing.

Lastly, a special type of ink will also have to be obtained.  The entire
contents of the vial of ink will be used up during the scribing process.

Scribing takes time and concentration.  Any interruption in the process will
destroy the work in progress and the components involved will be useless.
